./../cpp/align-cpp.md) `__declspec` modifier is not permitted on function parameters. Function parameter alignment is controlled by the calling convention used. For more information, see [Calling Conventions](../../cpp/calling-conventions.md).  \n  \n The following sample generates C2719 and shows how to fix it:  \n  \n```  \n// C2719.cpp  \nvoid func(int __declspec(align(32)) i);   // C2719  \n// try the following line instead  \n// void func(int i);  \n```"}